               <lb facs="#facs_71_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>to women and children who didn't have it before, in the ancient law, neither in the Roman nor in
               <lb facs="#facs_71_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>the Greek, and certainly not in the so-called barbarian cultures.
               <lb facs="#facs_71_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>Now this was an enlargement. The concept of the slave was reduced as somebody who is not
               <lb facs="#facs_71_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>equal in UITIMATE relations, and was finally abolished. But look here at the difficulty of the
